<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><img style="width: 879px; height: 452px;" src="/media/13072533/best-of-amalfi-coast-tour.jpg?width=879&amp;height=452&amp;mode=max" alt="Best of Amalfi Coast Private Tour" /></p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<div class="data-grid" style="float: center;">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" class="tablet-button" style="height: 50px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td height="20" align="center" valign="middle" style="background-color: #89aa4d; border-top-left-radius: 4px; border-bottom-left-radius: 4px; border-top-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-right-radius: 4px; background-clip: padding-box; font-size: 18px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; text-align: center; color: #ffffff; font-weight: bold; padding-left: 18px; padding-right: 18px;">For more information or to book our Twin Centre Holidays &amp; Tours please call 01483 79 11 11</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>Whether it is for a special occasion or travelling in a group, this private escorted tour is perfect for discovering the beauty of the <a data-udi="umb://document/f13578bcd0ea422bb13fbbbc34693d47" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f13578bcd0ea422bb13fbbbc34693d47}" title="Amalfi Coast">Amalfi Coast</a>. </p>
<p><strong>Day 1 </strong><br />Fly to Naples and be transferred to your hotel by your own private driver. </p>
<p><strong>Day 2 </strong><br />Today, meet your own private local guide and set off on your hiking tour on the lemon path. Visit the local Limoncello factory and enjoy a liqueur tasting experience.</p>
<p><strong>Day 3</strong> <br />This morning take a walking tour of the bustling town of <a data-udi="umb://document/1b38a4293ff04cc8b2dd360a57a538d8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1b38a4293ff04cc8b2dd360a57a538d8}" title="Sorrento">Sorrento</a>. Immerse yourselves in the local life at Piazza Tasso, where you can admire the Baroque architecture and watch the locals go by their day. In the afternoon head along the Amalfi Drive, one of the most beautiful routes in the world, passing the Belvedere of Positano where you can stop for a photo. Explore <a data-udi="umb://document/f13578bcd0ea422bb13fbbbc34693d47" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f13578bcd0ea422bb13fbbbc34693d47}" title="Amalfi Coast">Amalfi</a> and see its iconic sites, such as St Andrew's Dome &amp; Paradise Cloister. </p>
<p><span><strong>Day</strong> <strong>4 </strong><br /></span>A full day's excursion visit to the archaeological site of Pompeii and the fascinating volcano Vesuvius that destroyed the town in AD 79. This tour is a group tour however, we can organise an exclusive tour for you and your party. </p>
<p><strong>Day</strong> <strong>5 </strong><br />A day at leisure to relax and explore the town or head to the beach. </p>
<p><strong>Day</strong> <strong>6</strong><br />A day trip by boat to visit the pretty island of <a data-udi="umb://document/7883a5ede77b4681ac9221e4d68f0771" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7883a5ede77b4681ac9221e4d68f0771}" title="Island of Capri">Capri</a>. Full of stylish boutiques and restaurants along with breath taking views, the island of Capri will certainly not disappoint!</p>
<p><strong>Day</strong> <strong>7</strong> <br />Another free day to unwind before your departure, the following day.</p>
<p><strong>Day</strong> <strong>8</strong><br />Transfer to Naples airport for your return flight.</p>
</div>
